        dc:description           "Fig. 5. Orthotheres haliotidis Geiger & Martin, 1999. A–C, G, ovigerous female (12.7 × 8.8 mm) (AM P3155); D, E, H, ovigerous female (12.3 × 7.9 mm) (AM P3155); F, I–M, male (7.4 × 6.7 mm) (AM P72223). A, dorsal view of carapace; B, left MXP3 (setae not drawn); C, left MXP3 palp (lateral view, setae not drawn); D, left MXP3 (setae not drawn); E, left MXP3 palp (lateral view, setae not drawn); F, male abdomen; G, H, female abdominal somite 6 and telson; I, left G1 (ventral view); J, distal part of left G1 (ventral view, setae not drawn); K, left G1 (dorsal view, setae not drawn); L, distal part of left G1 (dorsal view, setae not drawn); M, left G2 (ventral view). Scale bars = 1.0 mm [A, F, G, H], 0.2 mm [B–E, I–M]." ;
